## Booking Status Lifecycle

```
pending
  ↓ (driver accepts)
accepted
  ↓ (admin clicks "Mark Dispatched" OR driver sets off)
dispatched
  ↓ (admin clicks "Mark Arrived" OR driver marks arrived)
arrived
  ↓ (driver completes trip)
completed

At any point before completion:
  → cancelled  (by driver or client — immediately propagated to all surfaces)

If driver denies:
  → denied     (admin notified, may reassign → back to pending)

If driver doesn't respond:
  → timed_out  (admin notified, may reassign → back to pending)
```

**Every status transition — whether triggered by admin, driver, or client — runs through the same backend broadcaster and propagates to all three surfaces instantly.**

