#### KPI Counter Row — 4 Cards (all live, all real-time)

| Card | Label | Value Source | Updates When |
|---|---|---|---|
| Ready | Drivers/ambulances with status `available` | `drivers` table | Driver goes online/offline, trip completes/cancels |
| Active | Bookings with status `accepted` or `dispatched` | `bookings` table | Driver accepts, trip completes, trip cancels |
| On Mission | Bookings with status `arrived` | `bookings` table | Driver marks arrived, trip completes |
| Pending Requests | Bookings with status `pending` | `bookings` table | New booking submitted, driver accepts/denies/times out |

**All four counters listen to `booking_status_update` and `driver_status_update` Socket.io events and re-compute their values instantly.**

On page load: fetch current counts from:
- `GET /drivers?status=available` → Ready count
- `GET /bookings?status=accepted,dispatched` → Active count
- `GET /bookings?status=arrived` → On Mission count
- `GET /bookings?status=pending` → Pending count

Do NOT hardcode zeros. Do NOT wait for the next event to populate — fetch on mount, then keep live via Socket.io.

