#### Real-Time Data Binding Summary for Overview Page

The Overview page must subscribe to these Socket.io events on mount and unsubscribe on unmount:

| Event | Effect on Overview |
|---|---|
| `new_booking` | +1 Pending counter; prepend card to Incoming Requests panel |
| `booking_status_update` { status: accepted } | -1 Pending; +1 Active; remove from Incoming Requests; add to Active Emergencies |
| `booking_status_update` { status: dispatched } | Active count stays; update Active Emergencies card status badge |
| `booking_status_update` { status: arrived } | -1 Active; +1 On Mission; update Active Emergencies card |
| `booking_status_update` { status: completed } | -1 On Mission or Active; remove from Active Emergencies |
| `booking_status_update` { status: cancelled } | Decrement whichever counter it was in; remove from Active Emergencies and/or Incoming Requests |
| `booking_status_update` { status: denied / timed_out } | -1 Pending; remove card from Incoming Requests |
| `driver_status_update` { status: available } | +1 Ready counter; update fleet map marker to green |
| `driver_status_update` { status: on_trip } | -1 Ready counter; update fleet map marker to red |
| `driver_status_update` { status: offline } | -1 Ready counter; update fleet map marker to grey |
| `ambulance_location_update` | Update driver marker position on fleet map |

**On socket reconnect:** re-fetch all four KPI counts from REST endpoints, re-fetch pending bookings list, and re-render fleet map markers from latest driver positions.

