**Status rows NEVER stay stale.** The table listens to `booking_status_update` and patches the row in-place the moment any status change occurs — including cancellations from either the driver or client side.

**Cancellation notification:**
When a booking is cancelled, a **toast notification** appears in the admin dashboard:
```
🔴  Booking #{id} cancelled
    Cancelled by: Driver  |  Reason: "Patient not reachable"
    Patient: [Name] — [Phone]
```

**Admin action buttons — status changes that propagate to ALL surfaces:**

The admin Live Monitor has context-sensitive action buttons per booking row. When the admin clicks any of these, the backend updates the database and **immediately broadcasts `booking_status_update` to the client, driver, and admin — all three simultaneously.**

| Button | Visible when status is | API call | New status | Driver receives | Client receives |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Mark Dispatched** | `accepted` | `PATCH /bookings/:id/dispatch` | `dispatched` | Screen updates to show "You are dispatched" state | Tracking page status banner updates to DISPATCHED |
| **Mark Arrived** | `dispatched` | `PATCH /bookings/:id/arrive` | `arrived` | Trip screen updates to arrived state | Tracking page updates to ARRIVED, ETA shows "Driver is here" |
| **Reassign** | `denied` or `timed_out` | `PATCH /bookings/:id/reassign` | `pending` | New driver receives the request in their overlay | Client tracking page shows "Finding a driver..." |

**The rule:** Admin clicking a status button is treated identically to the driver or client triggering that status change — the backend runs the same `statusBroadcaster` and emits `booking_status_update` to all three rooms. No surface stays in its old state.

**Admin fallback (reassignment):**
Admin can click **Reassign** on `denied` or `timed_out` bookings to select a different available driver. This resets the booking to `pending` and sends the request to the new driver's overlay.

