## 6. Real-Time Socket.io Event Map

All three surfaces join a booking room: `room:booking_{bookingId}`

| Event | Emitter | Listeners | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `join_driver_room` | Driver App | Server | Driver joins `driver_room_{driverId}` on connect/reconnect |
| `join_admin_monitor` | Admin Dashboard | Server | Admin joins `admin_monitor` room on connect |
| `new_booking` | Client App | Driver (primary), Admin (monitor) | Booking submitted — goes directly to driver |
| `driver_accepted` | Driver App | Client, Admin | Driver accepts — all surfaces update to `accepted` |
| `driver_denied` | Driver App | Admin | Driver denies — admin sees `denied`, can reassign |
| `booking_status_update` | **Backend** (on every status change) | **Client, Driver, Admin — ALL THREE** | Universal status sync event. Payload: `{ bookingId, status, cancelledBy?, cancelReason? }` |
| `booking_cancelled` | **Backend** (when status = cancelled) | Client, Driver, Admin | Explicit cancellation event with reason and who cancelled |
| `ambulance_location_update` | Driver App | Client, Admin | GPS every 5 seconds |
| `patient_location_update` | Client App | Driver, Admin | GPS every 5 seconds |
| `trip_completed` | Backend (on complete) | Client, Admin | Trip ended — rating page shown on client |
| `driver_status_update` | **Backend** (on every driver status change) | Admin (Overview + Monitor) | Driver goes available/on_trip/offline — updates KPI counters and fleet map markers |
| `payment_confirmed` | Admin | Client | Payment confirmed |

> **Key rule:** The backend is responsible for emitting `booking_status_update` to all rooms on **every** status change. No frontend should change status locally without a server confirmation first.

