## 9. Frontend Reconnect & State Reconciliation

On every socket reconnect (all three surfaces):

**Driver App:**
1. Re-join `driver_room_{driverId}`
2. Call `GET /bookings/active?driverId={id}` — this must fetch the latest booking with status `pending`, `accepted`, `dispatched`, or `arrived`.
   - If the status is `pending`, immediately trigger the incoming request overlay.
   - If the status is `accepted`/`dispatched`/`arrived`, restore the active trip screen.
   - If the status is `cancelled`/`completed`, clear the state and go to home screen.
3. Resume GPS emission if on active trip

**Client App:**
1. Re-join `room:booking_{bookingId}` (from persisted Zustand store)
2. Call `GET /bookings/:id` — sync latest status; if cancelled/completed, update screen accordingly
3. Resume patient GPS emission if booking is still active

**Admin Dashboard:**
1. Re-join `admin_monitor`
2. Call `GET /bookings` to refresh the full table and reconcile any status changes missed during disconnect
3. Call `GET /bookings?status=pending` to repopulate Incoming Requests panel on Overview
4. Call `GET /drivers` to repopulate fleet map markers and Ready counter on Overview

