## 12. Key Design Rules

1. **One login page, smart routing** — role detected server-side, redirect client-side
2. **Admins use email + password** — drivers use name + driver ID
3. **Drivers created by admin only** — no self-serve driver registration
4. **Requests go directly to the driver** — no admin approval gate
5. **Admin monitors, not dispatches** — sees everything in real-time but does not block the flow
6. **Status is always in sync across all three surfaces** — `booking_status_update` is emitted to all rooms on every change
7. **Cancellation propagates immediately both ways** — driver cancel notifies client; client cancel notifies driver; admin sees both
8. **`cancelled_by` and `cancel_reason` are always stored and visible to admin**
9. **No surface shows stale status** — every surface reconciles with the server on load and socket reconnect
10. **Admin Live Monitor is never stale** — rows update in-place in real-time; cancelled bookings never stay showing active
11. **Driver notifies completion via `trip_completed`** — client sees rating page, admin records it
12. **Admin fallback only** — admin reassigns only on `denied` or `timed_out` bookings
13. **Dispatch always shows real names** — Company + Driver Name + ID + call buttons
14. **SafeBoda-style driver request screen** — full-screen overlay, direct dispatch, 30s timeout
15. **Maps: Leaflet + OpenStreetMap everywhere** — no Google Maps, no API key needed
16. **Coordinate Safety** — every map marker validates lat/lng before rendering
17. **Socket Resilience** — all clients rejoin their rooms and reconcile state on reconnect
18. **Client Persistence** — active booking survives browser refresh via Zustand persist